  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Length: 3-5m

    Physical Description: Fleshy, hose-like organism.

    Origin:
    Extraterrestrial meteorite. Specific coordinates unknown.

    First Sighting:
    April 2, 2008. Subject reported waking to a loud crash and observing a cluster
    of giant, serpentine creatures through the window. Subject fled the premises
    in panic. The investigation team arrived three days later to find a new fountain
    array had manifested in the clearing.

    Behavioral Analysis: Gregarious, typically
    forming clusters of 10-20. Capable of secreting a concrete-like substance for
    nest construction. Nests are camouflaged as dry deck fountains for unknown reasons.
    Exhibits predatory play behavior; observed waiting for prey to lower defenses
    before ejecting high-pressure columns of red liquid to incapacitate. Feeding
    behavior has not yet been observed.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: c2f8dfd04e89639488cc43e3edabe142, type: 2}
